definition[0]: to fall onto the ground or to fall from an upright position
example[0]: Tommy fell over and cut his knee badly.
definition[1]: to hit your foot against something by mistake and fall to the ground
example[2]: She fell over the dog and broke her front teeth.
definition[2]: to be very eager to do something, especially something you do not usually do
example[3]: People were falling over themselves to help her.
